dc_title_s: Pottawattamie County, Iowa, 1955, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet labels. Images are photoreductions of mosaics created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BKP. Form of individual image numbering: BKP-1P-[number], BKP-2P-[number], or BKP-3P-[number]."Flying completed 7-30-55" Flown by Puckett Aerial Surveys, Inc. Louisville, Kentucky."Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
